race.comment: CAPPADORA (1) showed strong early pace from the wide draw and stuck on well despite missing the frame, finishing fifth over 300m this track in 17.30. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and two minor placings to her credit. Worth another chance. DOLLY DOTTY (2) went straight to the front and never headed when winning two back but could manage only midfield last time when finished 5th and beaten 8 lengths at Northam (17.81). Bold showing expected. OUTLAW MCGRAW (3) settled close to the lead but collided in the run and turned spotting a start, finishing sixth (20.43) at Northam over 297m in a Grade 5. Key player if finds best. MISS MONEY (6) placed here at this trip last start - cannot be ignored.
